SIMPLE: ping-pong
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ping-pong
<hw>ping"-pong`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Imitative.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An indoor modification of lawn tennis played with small
bats, or battledores, and a very light, hollow, celluloid ball, on a
large table divided across the middle by a net. Also called
<altname>table tennis</altname>.</def> <mark>[[originally a trade
name]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A size of photograph a little larger than a postage
stamp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ping-pong</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ping-pong
<hw>Ping"-pong`</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To play
ping-pong.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to bounce back and forth, in the manner of a
ping-pong ball.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ping-pong ball</ent>⟦br⟧
